LABORATORY
Reviewed his laboratory studies.  CBC and electrolyte panel are within normal limits.  CEA is 2.5.  Reviewed his CT chest, abdomen, and pelvis which shows no evidence of residual disease.
IMPRESSION, REPORT, AND PLAN
#1 Metastatic colon adenocarcinoma T3, NIB, MI status-post resection
Discussed with Mr. Lewis and his family that currently he has no evidence of residual disease.  He underwent an RO resection.  There is no evidence of tumor recurrence.  However, due to the fact that he had metastases at the time of presentation, we would recommend adjuvant therapy in the form of FOLFOX.  I discussed with him the side-effects associated with the FOLFOX regimen which includes but is not limited to nausea, vomiting, fatigue, myelosuppression, and risk for infection.  He will also require a Port-A-Cath placement.  We discussed the need for treatment which would be six-months in duration and on an every-two-week schedule.
#2 Dental abscesses
He currently has a dental abscess for which he has been treated with antibiotics.  We recommend addressing his dental issues prior to initiation of chemotherapy.
FOLLOW-UP PLAN
The patient will contact us after he has had his dental evaluation completed locally.
ADVANCE DIRECTIVES
Advance directive or living will: No, not interested in additional information.
PATIENT EDUCATION
Ready to learn, no apparent learning barriers were identified; learning preferences include listening.  Explained diagnosis and treatment plan; patient expressed understanding of the content.

